| first3 = R}}\n\n==Research==\n\n*\u201cContinuous Infusion Ropivacaine Intrascalene Blocks Versus Placebo after Arthroscopic Rotator Cuff Repair\u201d 013-2014 Co-Senior Author with Randy Schwartzberg, M.D., Firas Abdul, M.D.,  and Bradd Burkhart, M.D.\n*\u201cPre-operative Measurements of ACL Insertion Sites\u201d 2012-2013 Co-Senior Author with Randy Schwartzberg, M.D. and Kevin Snyder, M.D.\n*\u201cSafety of Transphyseal ACL Reconstruction in Skeletally-Immature Patients.\u201d Faculty investigator Angelo Colosimo, M.D. 2005-2006 Primary Investigator\n*\u201cFunctional and Biomechanical Evaluation of a New Shoulder Brace for Anterior Shoulder Instability.\u201d Faculty investigators Warren Harding III, M.D. and Robert Heidt, Jr., M.D. 2005-2006 Primary Investigator\n*\u201cCorrelation between MRI and MR-Arthrogram with Arthroscopic Findings in Patients with Type 2 SLAP Lesions.\u201d Faculty investigator Randy Schwartzberg, M.D. 2001-2005 Primary Investigator.\n*\u201cThe Timing of Formal Treatment and Its Effect on Open Tibial Shaft Fracture Infection and Nonunion Rate.\u201d Faculty Investigator JD Cole, M.D. 2001-2005 Primary Investigator.\n*\u201cShoulder Bracing for Anterior Shoulder Instability: An Expanded Update.\u201d Faculty Investigator Kevin Nowicki, M.D. 2003-2006 Primary Investigator.\n*[http://www.floridamd.com/orthopaedic/orlando-orthopaedic-center-foundation-supporting-cutting-edge-orthopaedic-research/ \"Efficacy of Continuous Infusion Ropivacaine Interscalene Blocks Versus Placebo for Pain Control After Arthroscopic Rotator Cuff Repair\"]\n*\"Cylindrical Bone Plug Creation Time and Efficacy Using Cylindrical Bone Grinder versus Rongeur in ACL Reconstruction.\" Faculty investigator Russ Alberts, M.D. 1998-1999 Primary Investigator.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reuss, Bryan L}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Omaha, Nebraska]]\n[[Category:American orthopedic surgeons]]\n[[Category:American sports physicians]]\n[[Category:University of Kansas alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Nebraska alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{orphan|date=September 2016}}\n{{notability|biography|date=September 2016}}\n{{external links|date=September 2016}}\n}}\n'''Bryan L. Reuss''' (born 1974 in Omaha, Nebraska) is an American orthopaedic surgeon. He received a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Biology with distinction from the [[University of Kansas]] in 1996 and graduated with honors with an M.D. from the [[University of Nebraska College of Medicine]] in 2000.<ref name=\"auto\"/> From 2000 to 2005, Dr. Reuss was an Orthopaedic Surgery Resident Physician in the [[Orlando Regional Healthcare]] System. In 2004-2005 he was awarded the \u201cResident of the Year\u201d for [[Orlando Regional Healthcare]] chosen from all the hospital system's Resident Doctors.<ref name=\"auto\"/> He completed an Orthopaedic Fellowship at the [[University of Cincinnati]]/Wellington Orthopaedics and Sports Medicine Fellowship in 2006.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=Bryan L. Reuss, M.D.|url=https://www.orlandoortho.com/physician/bryan-l-reuss-m-d/|website=www.orlandoortho.com/|accessdate=9 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916154328/https://www.orlandoortho.com/physician/bryan-l-reuss-m-d/|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2010, Dr. Reuss was awarded the Sports Medicine Person of the Year from the Athletic Trainers Association of Florida.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://seataorg.startlogic.com/eb03-22-11.htm|title=ATAF Annual Symposium & Award Winners: Dr. Cade Sportsmedicine Person of the Year|last=|first=|date=22 March 2011|work=SEATA eBlast News|access-date=12 July 2016|via=https://seataorg.startlogic.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916001013/https://seataorg.startlogic.com/eb03-22-11.htm|archive-date=16 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nReuss is Board Certified in [[orthopaedic surgery]] and is also Board Certified in [[sports medicine]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> He has been an orthopaedic surgeon at Orlando Orthopaedic Center since 2006.<ref name=\"auto\"/> He specializes in orthopaedic sports medicine, with a focus on minimally-invasive surgeries of the shoulder, hip, and knee. Reuss has been a guest speaker and keynote presenter at numerous orthopaedic conferences including presentations at the Florida Orthopaedic Society Annual Meeting,<ref>{{cite web|title=My \"Go-to\" Graft and Technique for ACL Reconstruction in Female Teenage Athlete|url=http://c.ymcdn.com/sites/www.floridaorthopediccommunity.com/resource/resmgr/2016_FOS_Annual_Meeting/Breakout_Agenda/2016_FOS_Sports_Breakout_Ses.pdf?hhSearchTerms=%22reuss%22|publisher=Florida Orthopaedic Society Scientific Annual Meeting 2016|accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref> the Annual Orlando Orthopaedic Center Sports Medicine Symposium, the Annual Orthopaedic Seminar for [[National Association of Orthopaedic Nurses]], the Florida Workman's Compensation Conference,<ref>{{cite web|title=A WCEC Session Preview: Lights! Cameras! Surgery!|url=http://www.wci360.com/news/article/a-wcec-session-preview-lights-cameras-surgery|website=www.wci360.com|publisher=Workers' Compensation Institute|accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref> the Annual Sports Medicine Congress, the FSARN Annual Meeting, the Florida Hospital Sports Medicine Symposium, the Orlando Health Orthopaedic Summit, the University of Central Florida, and the Athletic Trainers Association of Florida Annual Symposium. Reuss has performed live and webcast surgeries including a live knee meniscus repair surgery at the National Workers' Compensation Judiciary College in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|title=Live knee meniscus repair surgery|url=http://www.nawcj.org/docs/2010%20NAWCJ%20Judiciary%20College%20Handout.pdf|website=www.nawcj.org|publisher=National Workers' Compensation Judiciary College 2010|accessdate=12 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919160811/http://www.nawcj.org/docs/2010%20NAWCJ%20Judiciary%20College%20Handout.pdf|archive-date=19 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> a live ACL Reconstruction Surgery at the Orlando Orthopaedics Sports Medicine Symposium for Athletic Trainers and Physical Therapists, and in 2014 performed a live triceps repair and pre-recorded a live shoulder labrum repair for the 69th Annual Workers\u2019 Compensation Educational Conference<ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=Live Shoulder Labrum Repair|url=https://www.orlandoortho.com/live-surgery-event-workers-compensation-educational-conference/|publisher=69th Annual Workers' Compensation Educational Conference|access-date=2016-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916154325/https://www.orlandoortho.com/live-surgery-event-workers-compensation-educational-conference/|archive-date=2016-09-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> and the 26th Annual Safety and Health Conference.\n\n==Board, executive committee memberships and awards==\nReuss has served as Chairman of the Department of Orthopaedics for [[Orlando Health|Orlando Health Medical Center]] and as a Member of the Perioperative Governing Board, the Orthopaedic Medical Outcomes Committee, and on the Medical Executive Committee (Nominations Committee) for [[Orlando Health]] Medical Center.<ref name=\"auto\"/> He is an Advisory Board member for the Florida State Association of Rehabilitation Nurses and is a reviewer for the ''[[American Journal of Sports Medicine]]''.<ref name=\"auto\"/> Reuss is a board member of the MileSplit Medical Advisory Board with three other medical professionals: Gideon J. Lewis, Lisa Barkley, and Laura Podschun. He is a long-time member of the [[Arthroscopy Association of North America]], the National Athletic Trainers Association, and the Athletic Trainers Association of Florida.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nReuss has served on numerous board and committees including:\n*\tMember of Attorney General [[Bill McCollum]]\u2019s Healthcare Committee\n*\tPhysician\u2019s Council for Responsible Reform- Physician Consultant to Republican members of the [[United States Congress]]\n*\tCentral Florida Doctor Publication Advisory Board\n*\tVolunteer committee member for [[Special Olympics|Special Olympics Florida]]\n*\tSponsor and volunteer for Metropolitan Orlando Urban League-Youth Empowerment Program\n\nReuss has won several awards, including the 2010 Sports Medicine Person of the Year from the Athletic Trainers Association of Florida and the Florida Orthopaedic Society Injured Worker\u2019s Inspiration Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orlandoortho.com/dr-reuss-wins-2012-injured-workers-inspiration-award/|title=Dr. Reuss Wins 2012 Injured Workers Inspiration Award - Orlando Orthopaedic Center|date=20 August 2012}}</ref> In 2014, he won the Exemplary Physician Colleague Award from the Executive Nursing Leaders at Orlando Health.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.orlandoortho.com/exemplary-physician-colleague-award-presented-dr-reuss/|title=Exemplary Physician Colleague Award Presented to Dr. Reuss|date=8 April 2014}}</ref> As a resident, he won the 2004-2005 \u201cResident of the Year\u201d for [[Orlando Regional Healthcare]] chosen from all the hospital system's Resident Doctors and then received the \"Attending of the Year\" in 2014 for his efforts as a Sports Medicine faculty of the Orlando Health Orthopaedic Residency Program.  He also won first place in the 2007 Resident Writer's Competition for the American Journal of Orthopedics and first place in the 2005 Florida Orthopaedic Society Resident Research Competition.  In 2015, he was named as one of Orlando's \"Top Doctors\" and \"Best Doctors.\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.orlandomagazine.com/Orlando-Magazine/December-2015/Best-Doctors-2015/|title=Best Doctors 2015-2016 - Orlando Magazine - December 2015 - Orlando, FL|website=www.orlandomagazine.com|access-date=2016-06-22}}</ref> In 2016, Reuss was named one of the Best Doctors for Orthopaedic Surgery in Orlando Family magazine and also chosen as a Reader's Choice Best Doctor, Orthopaedic Surgery by the readers of the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Doctors|url=http://www.orlandofamilymagazine.com/current-issue/best-doctors/|website=Orlandofamilymagazine.com|publisher=Orlando Family Magazine|accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Faculty positions and professorships==\n*\t[[University of Central Florida College of Medicine]] [https://med.ucf.edu/directory/profile/bryan-l-reuss/ Clinical Faculty] from 2009 to present<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reuss|first1=Bryan|title=UCF College of Medicine: Bryan L Reuss|url=https://med.ucfhttps://med.ucf.edu/directory/profile/bryan-l-reuss/|website=UCF College of Medicine|accessdate=6 July 2016}}</ref>\n*\t[[Arthrex|Arthrex Teaching Faculty]]- National Educator for Orthopaedic Surgeons from 2010 to present \n*\tOrlando Health Orthopaedic Residency Program Sports Medicine Clinical Faculty from 2006 to 2014 \n*\t[[Nova Southeastern University]] Physician Assistant Program, Clinical Faculty from 2009 to 2011\n\n==Sports physician positions==\nReuss has been a physician for the following sports teams and entertainment venues:\n\nCurrent:<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n*\t[https://web.archive.org/web/20160918184927/http://www.orlandopredators.com/team/medical-team Team Physician] for the [[Orlando Predators]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reuss|first1=Bryan|title=Medical Team - Orlando Predators|url=http://www.orlandopredators.com/team/medical-team|website=www.orlandopredators.com|publisher=Orlando Predators|accessdate=6 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526021103/http://www.orlandopredators.com/team/medical-team|archive-date=26 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*       Physician for PGA's [[Arnold Palmer Invitational]]\n*\tAssociate Physician for [[Cirque du Soleil|Cirque Du Soleil, La Nouba]], Orlando, FL\n*\tHead Team Physician for [[Boone High School]], Orlando, FL\n*\tAssociate Physician for [https://web.archive.org/web/20161020065219/https://www.seminolestate.edu/athletics/athletic-training/staff Seminole State College]\n*\tAssociate Physician for [[Bethune-Cookman University]]\n*\tAssociate Team Physician for [[Lake Brantley High School]], [[Lyman High School]], [[University High School (Orlando, Florida)|University High School]], [[Apopka High School]], [http://www.trinityprep.org/ Trinity Prep High School], [[Paul J. Hagerty High School|Hagerty High School]], [[Oviedo High School]], [[Winter Springs High School]], [[Timber Creek High School]], [https://web.archive.org/web/20160916210110/https://www.ocps.net/lc/east/her/pages/default.aspx East River High School] [https://web.archive.org/web/20160916204741/https://www.ocps.net/lc/southeast/hco/Pages/default.aspx Colonial High School], [http://www.lakemaryprep.com/school/about?st-t=google_adwords&campaignid=180882813&keyword=%2Blake%20%2Bmary%20%2Bpreparatory Lake Mary Prep High School], and [[Maynard Evans High School|Evans High School]]\nPast:<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n*\t[[Cincinnati Bengals]] Assistant Team Physician 2005-2006\n*\t[[University of Cincinnati]] Athletics Assistant Team Physician 2005-2006\n*\t[[NFL Combine]] Physician 2006\n*\t[[ATP Masters Series]] (Professional Tennis Tour) Physician 2005 \u2013 2006\n*\t[[USA Boxing]] Physician 2008\n*\t[[United Football League (2009\u201312)|United Football League]] 2009-2010\n*\t[[East\u2013West Shrine Game|East-West Shrine Game]] 2010-2011\n*\t[[Atlantic 10 Conference|A-10 Conference]]  Basketball Tournament 2010\n*\t[[USA Rugby]] 2004\n*\t[[Campbell County High School (Kentucky)|Campbell County High School]] Team Physician 2005-2006\n\n==Publications==\n\n*{{cite journal | pmid = 26779556 | doi=10.1177/2325967115623212 | volume=4 | issue=1 | title=High Prevalence of Superior Labral Tears Diagnosed by MRI in Middle-Aged Patients With Asymptomatic Shoulders | pmc=4710128 | year=2016 | journal=Orthop J Sports Med | page=2325967115623212  | last1 = Schwartzberg | first1 = R | last2 = Reuss | first2 = BL | last3