|\"2.5\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[The Good Doctor (TV series)|The Good Doctor]]''\n|Kerry\u015b Husband\n|Guest (season 3 episode 11)\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2475161|name=Tongai Arnold Chirisa}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chirisa, Tongayi}}\n[[Category:Zimbabwean male film actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean male television actors]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Zimbabwean male actors]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Lomagundi College]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n\n\n{{zimbabwe-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n|name = Tongayi Chirisa\n|image = \n|image_size =\n|alt = \n|caption = \n|birth_name = Tongayi Arnold Chirisa\n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1981|8|8}}\n|birth_place = [[Zimbabwe]]\n|death_date =\n|death_place =\n|nationality = [[Zimbabwean]]\n|other_names = \n|alma_mater = {{unbulleted list| [[AFDA, The South African School of Motion Picture Medium and Live Performance|The South African School of Motion Picture Medium and Live Performance]]}}\n|occupation = Actor, singer ,poet\n|known_for = Acting \n|spouse = \n|children = \n|parents = \n|relations = \n}}\n\n'''Tongayi Arnold Chirisa''' (born 8 August 1981) is a [[Zimbabwe]]an actor known for playing [[Man Friday]] on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Crusoe (TV series)|Crusoe]]'' television series, Father Nicholas on ''[[The Jim Gaffigan Show]]'', and Hekule on [[Leon Schuster]]'s ''[[Mr. Bones 2: Back from the Past]]'' movie. He is experienced in theatre, film, and television, and is also an occasional singer.\n\n==Education==\nChirisa attended [[Lomagundi College]].<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.zimnewsblog.com/news/chirisa-traces-journey-to-hollywood/ | title =Chirisa traces journey to Hollywood | date =2015-08-02 | publisher =Zim News Blog | access-date =2017-10-28 | quote =I proceeded to \u2018A\u2019 Level (Lomagundi College) }}</ref> He also studied for a Bachelor of Arts in Live Performance at [[AFDA, The School for the Creative Economy]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Quinn|first=Nicola|title=Chirisa gains Hollywood fame|url=https://www.newsday.co.zw/2015/07/chirisa-gains-hollywood-fame/|accessdate=February 18, 2018|work=[[NewsDay (Zimbabwean newspaper)|NewsDay]]|date=July 6, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nHe played the part of \"Detective Trevor Davies\" in the popular Zimbabwean soapie ''Studio 263''.<ref>http://www.thezimbabwestandard.com/entertainment/14154.html</ref> He also appeared in numerous feature films, the most well known being ''[[Tanyaradzwa]]'' in 2004, for which he won the Best Actor for Film and Television Award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0920869/|title=Tanyaradzwa|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> He has also featured in music videos and is a singer. He also starred in a serial radio drama Mopani Junction that was taken off air at the height of political turmoil in Zimbabwe.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}} He has been nominated and won many NAMA Awards over the last five years. He recently played the lead in the comedy feature film ''[[Mr Bones 2: Back from the Past]]''. He made a dramatic appearance in the mini-series ''Rough'' directed by British director, [[Andy Wilson (director)|Andy Wilson]], appeared in an international feature film ''Skin'', directed by Anthony Fabian and co-starring Sam Neill, and played a lead in a local drama series ''Redemption'' for [[SABC 1]]. He played [[Man Friday]] on the [[NBC]] international television series ''[[Crusoe (TV series)|Crusoe]]'', based on the classic story ''[[Robinson Crusoe]]''.<ref>http://www.nbc.com/Crusoe/</ref> He also appeared in ''[[Sleepy Hollow (TV series)|Sleepy Hollow]]'' based on [[The Legend of Sleepy Hollow]] by [[Washington Irving]]. He played Father Nicholas on ''[[The Jim Gaffigan Show]]'' (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvland.com/shows/the-jim-gaffigan-show/bios/tongayi-chirisa|title=Father Nicholas Ngugumbane/Tongayi Charisa/TV Land|website=TVLand|accessdate=September 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sundaynews.co.zw/chirisa-finds-love/|title=Chirisa finds love|first=The Sunday|last=News|website=The Sunday News}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2005\n|''Tanyaradzwa''\n|\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|''Ace of Hearts''\n|Tebsane Masa\n|Short\n|-\n|2008\n|''Zimbabwe''\n|Charles\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Skin (2008 film)|Skin]]''\n|Township Priest\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Mr. Bones 2: Back from the Past]]''\n|Hekule\n|\n|-\n|2009\n|''Gargoyle''\n|Themba\n|Short\n|-\n|2011\n|''Geezas''\n|Sammy the Mouth\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''Stand By''\n|Dee\n|Short\n|-\n|2014\n|''Whipping Boy''\n|Olly 'Napalm' Harris\n|Short\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Happiness Is a Four-letter Word]]''\n|Thomas\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''{{sortname|The|Zim|nolink=1}}''\n|William Zimunya\n|Short\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Antebellum (film)|Antebellum]]''\n|\n| ''Post-production''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2008\u201309\n|''[[Crusoe (TV series)|Crusoe]]''\n|[[Man Friday|Friday]]\n|Main role\n|-\n|2009\n|''Diamonds''\n|Oba Sewele\n|TV film\n|-\n|2010\n|''Mrs Mandela''\n|Arguing husband\n|TV film\n|-\n|2010\n|''Barack Obama's Cousin''\n|Barack Obama's Cousin\n|TV miniseries\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]]''\n|Interrogator\n|\"Betrayal\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[American Horror Story: Asylum]]''\n|Miles\n|\"[[Dark Cousin]]\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[H+: The Digital Series]]''\n|African Soldier\n|\"African Aid\", \"Seeds\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Sleepy Hollow (TV series)|Sleepy Hollow]]''\n|Arthur Bernard\n|\"The Sin Eater\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''Gaffigan''\n|Father Nicholas Ngungumbane\n|TV film\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Whitney (2015 film)|Whitney]]''\n|Gary Houston\n|TV film\n|-\n|2015\u201316\n|''{{sortname|The|Jim Gaffigan Show}}''\n|Father 